forthhishandtoholdtheark;fortheoxenstumbled.
13:10AndtheangeroftheLORDwaskindledagainstUzza,andhesmote
him,becauseheputhishandtotheark:andtherehediedbeforeGod.
13:11AndDavidwasdispleased,becausetheLORDhadmadeabreach
uponUzza:whereforethatplaceiscalledPerezuzzatothisday.
13:12AndDavidwasafraidofGodthatday,saying,HowshallIbring
thearkofGodhometome?13:13SoDavidbroughtnotthearkhometo
himselftothecityofDavid,butcarrieditasideintothehouseof
ObededomtheGittite.
