mineiniquity.
10:15IfIbewicked,woeuntome;andifIberighteous,yetwillI
notliftupmyhead.Iamfullofconfusion;thereforeseethoumine
affliction;10:16Foritincreaseth.Thouhuntestmeasafiercelion:
andagainthoushewestthyselfmarvellousuponme.
10:17Thourenewestthywitnessesagainstme,andincreasestthine
indignationuponme;changesandwarareagainstme.
10:18Whereforethenhastthoubroughtmeforthoutofthewomb?Oh
thatIhadgivenuptheghost,andnoeyehadseenme!10:19Ishould
havebeenasthoughIhadnotbeen;Ishouldhavebeencarriedfrom
thewombtothegrave.
