69:7BecauseforthysakeIhavebornereproach;shamehathcoveredmy
face.
69:8Iambecomeastrangeruntomybrethren,andanalienuntomy
mother'schildren.
69:9Forthezealofthinehousehatheatenmeup;andthereproaches
ofthemthatreproachedtheearefallenuponme.
69:10WhenIwept,andchastenedmysoulwithfasting,thatwastomy
reproach.
69:11Imadesackclothalsomygarment;andIbecameaproverbto
them.
69:12Theythatsitinthegatespeakagainstme;andIwasthesong
ofthedrunkards.
