32:1Behold,akingshallreigninrighteousness,andprincesshall
ruleinjudgment.
32:2Andamanshallbeasanhidingplacefromthewind,andacovert
fromthetempest;asriversofwaterinadryplace,astheshadowof
agreatrockinawearyland.
32:3Andtheeyesofthemthatseeshallnotbedim,andtheearsof
themthathearshallhearken.
32:4Theheartalsooftherashshallunderstandknowledge,andthe
tongueofthestammerersshallbereadytospeakplainly.
