63:1WhoisthisthatcomethfromEdom,withdyedgarmentsfrom
Bozrah?thisthatisgloriousinhisapparel,travellinginthe
greatnessofhisstrength?Ithatspeakinrighteousness,mightyto
save.
63:2Whereforeartthouredinthineapparel,andthygarmentslike
himthattreadethinthewinefat?63:3Ihavetroddenthewinepress
alone;andofthepeopletherewasnonewithme:forIwilltreadthem
inmineanger,andtrampletheminmyfury;andtheirbloodshallbe
sprinkleduponmygarments,andIwillstainallmyraiment.
63:4Forthedayofvengeanceisinmineheart,andtheyearofmy
redeemediscome.
63:5AndIlooked,andtherewasnonetohelp;andIwonderedthat
therewasnonetouphold:thereforemineownarmbroughtsalvation
untome;andmyfury,itupheldme.
63:6AndIwilltreaddownthepeopleinmineanger,andmakethem
drunkinmyfury,andIwillbringdowntheirstrengthtotheearth.
63:7IwillmentionthelovingkindnessesoftheLORD,andthepraises
oftheLORD,accordingtoallthattheLORDhathbestowedonus,and
thegreatgoodnesstowardthehouseofIsrael,whichhehathbestowed
